      <!-- Section 7 -->
      <section id="hallucinations" class="anchor-top prose-dark mb-16">
        <h2>Using Entity Optimisation to Reduce AI Hallucinations</h2>

        <p>
          <strong>AI hallucinations about brands — wrong product names, incorrect founding dates, misattributed services, fabricated executives — are almost always symptoms of weak entity authority.</strong>
          They occur when a model has insufficient, contradictory, or low-confidence data about an entity and generates a plausible-sounding
          but inaccurate response rather than acknowledging uncertainty.
        </p>

        <h3>Why Hallucinations Occur</h3>

        <p>
          When a large language model encounters a query about an entity with sparse representation in its training data,
          it faces a choice: abstain from answering (which it will typically do only if it has very low confidence),
          or generate a response by pattern-matching from similar entities. The result is a description that may blend attributes
          from multiple similar organisations, apply industry averages, or confidently state details that are simply wrong.
        </p>

        <p>
          Inconsistent entity data compounds this problem. A model trained on sources where your brand is described differently —
          as a "GEO agency", a "digital marketing consultancy", and a "content marketing service" — may generate a different
          description every time it is asked about you, pulling from different parts of its training data depending on
          the phrasing of the query.
        </p>

        <h3>The Entity Optimisation Fix</h3>

        <p>
          The remedy is systematic entity authority building. Each high-quality, consistent entity signal added to your record
          increases the model's confidence in your canonical description and reduces the probability of pattern-matched hallucination.
          The sequence that produces the fastest improvement in AI accuracy is:
        </p>

        <ol>
          <li><strong>Audit and standardise</strong> all existing entity data for consistency.</li>
          <li><strong>Deploy complete Organisation schema</strong> with a comprehensive <code>sameAs</code> array on your homepage.</li>
          <li><strong>Create or correct your Wikidata entry</strong> with accurate, sourced claims.</li>
          <li><strong>Update Google Business Profile</strong> to match your canonical record exactly.</li>
          <li><strong>Correct inconsistencies</strong> in Crunchbase, LinkedIn, and industry directories.</li>
          <li><strong>Build editorial corroboration</strong> through press, partnerships, and analyst relations over time.</li>
        </ol>

        <p>
          Monitor the results by systematically prompting AI systems with questions about your brand and recording how they describe you.
          As your entity record strengthens, you should observe a reduction in hallucinations and an increase in citation frequency
          and accuracy across ChatGPT, Perplexity, Gemini, and Copilot. For the full strategic context,
          see our <a href="/ai-brand-visibility/">AI brand visibility guide</a> and the
          <a href="/geo-services/#entity-optimisation">entity optimisation service</a> page.
        </p>
      </section>

